oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Cannon County 4-H Soil Judging Team
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Hogan, C.A., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Cannon County 4-H team. Land Judging that was first place winner in the District Four 4-H contest held at the Plateau Experiment Station.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
Left to right: Bobby Melton, Johnny Travis, thrid place individual winner; Eugene Bryan, County Agent, Jimmy Brandon and Ray C. Todd.
